smartMirror.dataModels.widgetsModels.weatherModels

Class Weather

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • smartMirror.dataModels.widgetsModels.weatherModels.Weather

  • public class Weather
extends java.util.Observable
    Author:
    CodeHigh @copyright on 07/12/2016. The weather object here stores the information related to the weather of the city that we call. It will store the current, maximum and minimum temperature along with the description and icon of the weather. Public getters and setters can be used to view any of the above mentioned variables.
